reviews.text: Have been coming here for years. They always have a wide range beer selection and their cocktails are great. We like to visit on Tuesdays where you can get a pitcher of beer and pizza for $25. Their trivia nights are fun too. Sometimes they will have themed trivia nights. We always get their chicken tender platter on the appetizer menu. It comes from Matty‚Äòs kitchen, and it‚Äôs really good! You can‚Äôt go wrong with their wings either.

Eli Fish is one of the most underrated spots in Western New York. Amazing beer with a huge selection--24 taps! Good cocktail program too. Shuffleboard, pool, live music in the square on the weekends in the summer, live music inside in the winter. Chicken fingers are homemade and incredible. I especially love their sour beers. Great vibes worth a visit.

Cool spot with a nice selection of of ciders to pick from. Portions are really good for the price and definitely full of flavor. Definitely will be back to try more. I went with the pork belly rice bowl. And she went with the grilled chicken rice bowl.

Pit stopped here on our road trip. We found parking right out front Tuesday evening. We were sat right away and immediately attended to. They offer a beer Flight for $12. We ordered the Amoreus, Senor Pescado, Maple Sunshine & Eli's Horchata Cream Ale.

The Amoreus was pretty good, a light and refreshing Lager. The Maple Sunshine was really interesting, you can definitely smell and taste the Maple and it leaves a sweet taste in your mouth. I really liked the Horchata Cream Ale, it tastes kind of like Cream soda. The Senor Pescado was also crisp and refreshing.

To eat, we ordered the Grit Cakes and the Pork Belly Rice Bowl. We did want to order the crab rangoon dip but they didn't have any. Food came pretty quickly. The Grit Cakes were light and fluffy and very good and crispy. They're quite big though and it comes with 4 large pieces. I did like the pork belly rice bowl as well but didn't fully enjoy the Chipotle ranch dip that we got on the side mixed.

Overall, a cool place to stop into and the beers are good. Friendly service and quiet. They do have a lot of seating indoors and a patio thats open as well.

We were passing through Batavia, New York on a Monday night. It looked like the only brewery in town that was open was the Eli Fish Brewing Company. The menu looked intriguing and the beer sounded good. We were not disappointed. Service was wonderful. We were promptly greeted by a friendly hostess who welcomed us. She accepted that we  were traveling brewery tourists, and got us a sticker to share with our local Brewery. Our waitress promptly offered Waters and multiple menus. I will share some of those, but the regular menu was too extensive to copy here. We chose the Schwartz beer and the Vienna Lager. Those were quite acceptable. I would have no problem coming back for more of those another night.  I had the Maple Sunshine for dessert, which was more of an acquired taste. The pizza of the month, McKenna's Bruschetta, was quite wonderful with a thick but light tasting crust, just the right amount of cheese and lots of flavor with the oil and garlic base, mozzarella, grilled chicken and fresh bruschetta. A side salad was not on the menu, but they provided one, which proved perfect for my wife. The place will seat quite a crowd, so I doubt you will be shut out if you show up on a busier night than a Monday. They even have games to keep the kids busy if you want to spend a little more. (I think parents always love a chance to have the kids busy somewhere else.) I have to give this place a 5/5. If you are passing through or a local, keep it in mind.

Stopped in for lunch with mom last week. We were sat quickly and had drinks shortly after. We ordered an app of mushroom caps which was fantastic. I had the burger and mom had a chipotle chicken wrap. Again, all great. Staff were friendly and bill was reasonable. I will be coming back to try about 47 more of their beers. Thanks!
Update: 3/22. Poor waitress was overworked. Way too many tables. She did the best she could but just wasn‚Äôt around enough.

detailedReviews.author: Rick Vattimo
detailedReviews.text: Love this place. Huge space but still retains a nice atmosphere. They have their own excellent beer on tap and the food is surprisingly good. Fun games all over the place as well and different events at night keep things fresh. Service can be spotty.

detailedReviews.author: Lee M.D.
detailedReviews.text: Great food and drinks . Awesome atmosphere. Zero complaints .

detailedReviews.author: Roger Thomas
detailedReviews.text: We were passing through Batavia, and dropped into this place based on a web search. What a local treasure! The atmosphere is casual and welcoming, the food is tremendous, the service is responsive, and the selection of drinks is broad. They've not only a great assortment of beers and ales, but also ciders, wine, and mixed drinks. Furthermore, the place is family-friendly! I saw many families with children enjoying their delicious meals, and they fit right in. We'll certainly be seeking out this venue next time we're in Batavia.

detailedReviews.author: Gary Colotti
detailedReviews.text:
Absolutely delicious meals. We were a party of 4,  no one got their burger cooked as desired however. Not a very big deal, but worth mentioning.

Update: we were a party of 6 on Friday, February 14. Valentines day. They sold out of 2 specials we were not made aware of until they took our order. We had already had drinks, and appetizers. We should have been made aware of the specials being sold out when we arrived. 2 of our party were only there for the specials. We were extremely disappointed, and we most likely will not be returning.

detailedReviews.author: Leah Cargill
detailedReviews.text: The jalape√±o poppers are absolutely incredible. I usually don‚Äôt seek out anything spicy, but these are worth every bite. Matty‚Äôs pizza is always a hit as well. Despite Eli Fish being a massive location with high ceilings, you can comfortably hear conversation at your table. Trivia Nights on Wednesday are a blast as well.

detailedReviews.author: Jerry N
detailedReviews.text:
Jambalaya was very good.
Service top notch.
Beer variety is always great.
Large place with lots of seating.
Parking on street.
Miss the roast beef on potatoes tho.
Menu is thin but everything is good.

detailedReviews.author: rich kozlowski
detailedReviews.text: Beer was amazing. Flights gave me a chance to expand on a few and found a new favorite! Food was good but alittle pricey. Great service and no wait at door.

detailedReviews.author: Mike Poler
detailedReviews.text: Great brewery with some phenomenal beers in my opinion, been here a few times.  Food was very good- had brisket rice bowl, French onion, mozzarella sticks ( these were huge) and fish nugs ( it was a special, might have the name wrong). Nice large venue.  Customer service was spot on- super friendly.

detailedReviews.author: Thom Grabar
detailedReviews.text: Ordered pick up, and was impressed by the dining room. It's a very nice place. Pick up was quick and easy. The food is a different story however. I had a pretty big order for my family and spent over $100. I got The Brewhouse Jambalaya, and it was a scam. The order describes what you would expect based on the name. A mix of chicken, sausage and shrimp over rice in a spicy broth. What I got was rice with 6 jumbo, tailed shrimp. Literally no sausage or chicken in this thing at all. Not a single piece of either. I was beyond disappointed, I don't even particularly like shrimp, I almost told them to skip it. But given the fact it's jambalaya I expected more sausage than anything, paired with a couple pieces of shrimp and chicken. So would I have gotten soupy rice for $20 if I said hold the shrimp? I genuinely feel robbed. Maybe they forgot to put the ingredients in mine, but I won't gamble spending almost $20 for this dish again.

detailedReviews.author: Cynthia Love
detailedReviews.text: Traveling through Batavia stopped here for lunch. Hostess was friendly and seated us quickly. Our waitress was very sweet, but was slow on delivering any requests, such as refills, etc.  The atmosphere was so uniquely decorated; industrial- meets - old time diner- meets- steampunk. Truly fantastic and great space. I enjoyed the brisket rice bowl. My friend had the chicken wrap, which met basic expectations, but the beer cheese Mac and cheese was truly disappointing. It was a very thin, salty sauce.

detailedReviews.author: Michael Weber
detailedReviews.text: Food is always amazing!! Never disappoints! The pretzel sticks are the best we have had.

detailedReviews.author: Rob Reed
detailedReviews.text:
Service can be a bit slower due to how busy they get, but that's still something to be aware of when coming here.
Food is awesome, so are the drink options.
Atmosphere is very loud but still allows for conversation at your own table.

detailedReviews.author: Luke Harding
detailedReviews.text: Had a private party in the back, Cadence and Alyssa rocked and were very attentive to our needs and we are not easy to please. A++. Highly recommend Eli fish for your next party

detailedReviews.author: Jason Hutchinson
detailedReviews.text: Amazing place. Huge inside and staff is great. We will be back!!

detailedReviews.author: Patty Benda Scotto
detailedReviews.text: Great selection of Craft beer, and food is always great, service is friendly and great

detailedReviews.author: Ted Irwin
detailedReviews.text:
I had the brisket with mac and cheese and cornbread. My wife had a burger and French onion soup.
Brisket was tender and juicy, cut nice and thick. Mac and cheese was on point. Burger was very jucy and flavourful. Soup was loaded with onions and cheese very rich and delicious.
Only complaints with the food the corn bread was a little dry and I prefer a thicker bark on my brisket.

Wide variety off beer and cider to meet anyone's pallet. The flight and can I had were excellent. Sours weren't bitter nor to sweet. October fest was wonderfully matly. The midnight reserve was warming reminded me of a nice pour of vanilla whiskey.

The mix and march can fridge and crowler options were great if you wanted to take drinks home.

detailedReviews.author: James DiFalco
detailedReviews.text: Great place to eat I had amazing service and the food was delicious.

detailedReviews.author: Kristy P
detailedReviews.text: Came here on a Monday just before 6. The servers were great about taking our group's orders so that we could take advantage of happy hour, however, there was nothing vegetarian/pescetarian on the HH menu so I couldn't take advantage of the specials. I enjoyed a flight of beers (and was happy to see they have a wide variety of styles!). All of our food was delivered promptly. I ended up ordering the mahi sandwich, and it was delicious, so I didn't feel as bad that I had to pay full price. Looking forward to coming here again, but hope there are more veggie friendly options (other than salads) in the future.

detailedReviews.author: Geoff Walton
detailedReviews.text:
What an amazing find.  The wings - crispy and hot - exactly what I hoped for. The pizza pepperoni, bacon, cherry hots, hot honey - wow.  Then there is the beer‚Ä¶ the selection is deep and outstanding- the Beautiful Midnight aged 3 years in Buffalo Trace barrels is brilliant , the two IPAs I sampled (full pour üòÄ) ‚Ä¶ needless to say I‚Äôll be taking a few selections to go.
Finally the staff - top notch, engaging, knowledgeable and busting it out on a Saturday evening. Seriously thank you. This is a must revisit.

detailedReviews.author: magoosmom1
detailedReviews.text: Still great.  Great selection of beers and food. Never disappoints

detailedReviews.author: Michael Knorr
detailedReviews.text:
Have been going to Eli since shortly after it opened and have become somewhat of a regular there. There have been ebbs and flows in the quality of the food and service due to staff turnover at times but they have never failed to make things right. Overall, I love the rotating selection of beers (though Bad, Bad Leroy Brown is never on tap long enough!) and the menu has kept this chubby guy satisfied. We have seen several restaurants in the center space but love that Matty's Pizza seems to be there to stay.

The atmosphere can be loud but that should be expected in such a large, old building. They have made several improvements to the space since opening and I've always felt comfortable there. Keep in mind it is a craft brewery first and foremost, so if you're expecting a quiet, pinkies out type meal this probably isn't the place for you. I've seen a lot of larger groups and families with kids of all ages happily dining there before though. We've taken guests from out of town on multiple occasions and they've always been able to find food and drink that they were happy with.

negative.author: Thom Grabar
negative.text: Ordered pick up, and was impressed by the dining room. It's a very nice place. Pick up was quick and easy. The food is a different story however. I had a pretty big order for my family and spent over $100. I got The Brewhouse Jambalaya, and it was a scam. The order describes what you would expect based on the name. A mix of chicken, sausage and shrimp over rice in a spicy broth. What I got was rice with 6 jumbo, tailed shrimp. Literally no sausage or chicken in this thing at all. Not a single piece of either. I was beyond disappointed, I don't even particularly like shrimp, I almost told them to skip it. But given the fact it's jambalaya I expected more sausage than anything, paired with a couple pieces of shrimp and chicken. So would I have gotten soupy rice for $20 if I said hold the shrimp? I genuinely feel robbed. Maybe they forgot to put the ingredients in mine, but I won't gamble spending almost $20 for this dish again.
